		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I thought it would be really cool to make a diagonal-based D-pad specifically for isometric games (ignore the bad photoshop):<br /><br /><img src="http://i498.photobucket.com/albums/rr343/JediQuestMaster/isometric_gamepad_zpsf9b36993.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Not sure how it would work though. Maybe just flip the controls 45 degrees right like most Rare games? Or pressing both top buttons triggers the 'Up' button? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" /> <br /><br />Of course, you can just <a href="http://www.romhacking.net/hacks/1211/" class="postlink">hack</a> a game to change its controls, but that's no fun. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" />

		

