	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, I figured Joust was just a 2-way direction stick, which would be sensible (i.e. cheaper) if you make the sticks yourself, which I presume Williams might have since they were a pinball machine manufacturer.<br /><br />If you're a hobbyist trying to build your own authentic-feeling Joust cabinet, I dunno how easy it would be to find a real 2-way stick these days. If you're scavenging used parts, I'd assume 4/8-way sticks are more common, and mechanically limiting one into a 2-way might be easiest? (I'm just speculating.)<br /><br />On a related note, does anyone remember those bizarre Defender controls? A 2-way up-down stick and then a whooooole lot of other buttons.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


